<span id="freeTextContainer15241898713187706163">4.5<br/><br/>Every time I read a classic Russian fiction that’s as philosophical and edifying as it is entertaining, I inevitably wonder why I bother reading anything else. That’s the way it goes. Chekhov is beautifully and casually expressive, and these novellas stimulate both the head and heart. They thrum with ideologies, they’re tense with passionate, searching, pathetic, wonderful characters, and they glow with their compassion and art.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


